# Refactoring Remaining Utilities to Domain-Driven Design (DDD)

We are eliminating the generic `src/utils/` directory to strictly adhere to Clean Architecture/DDD. We will migrate the remaining functions (`auth.ts`, `naming.ts`, `url.ts`) to appropriate semantic locations.

## Proposed Changes

### Deletion of Obsolete Code

#### [DELETE] `src/utils/`
- Once all external references are updated, remove the entire generic utility folder.

### Domain Layer Additions

#### [NEW] `src/domain/value-objects/Slug.ts`
- **Purpose**: Encapsulate the logic of converting strings to URL-friendly slugs (currently `toSlug` in `url.ts`).
- **Implementation**: A Value Object class that takes a string, normalizes it, removes accents, and formats it.
- **Usage**: Update `SyncLearningPath` and `SyncCourseData` to use `Slug.create(text).value`.

#### [NEW] `src/domain/value-objects/PlatformUrl.ts`
- **Purpose**: Encapsulate URL sanitization rules specific to the platform (currently `sanitizeUrl` in `url.ts`).
- **Implementation**: A Value Object that throws if the URL is completely invalid, and exposes a sanitized string (removing double slashes).
- **Usage**: Update `DownloadVideos` and tests to use this instead of `sanitizeUrl()`.

#### [NEW] `src/domain/services/AssetNamingService.ts`
- **Purpose**: Encapsulate the complex business rules for naming downloaded asset files sequentially and safely (currently `getAssetFilename` in `naming.ts`).
- **Implementation**: A stateless Domain Service with a static method or instance method `generateSafeFilename(metadataTitle, orderIndex)`.
- **Usage**: Update instances in `DownloadGuides`, `DownloadVideos`, `renameVideos.ts`, `verifyAssetFiles.ts`, `captureCourseTraffic.ts`, and `interceptor.ts`.

### Testing Updates

#### [MODIFY] `src/tests/utils/utils.test.ts`
- Rename to `src/tests/domain/value-objects/Slug.test.ts` / `PlatformUrl.test.ts` / `AssetNamingService.test.ts` as appropriate, adapting the existing test suite to the new classes.

### Final Clean Up

#### [DELETE] `src/utils/`
- Once all external references are updated, remove the entire generic utility folder.
